casebody.data:
MOTION AND PROCEDURAL RULINGS

2009-1292. State ex rel. Doner v. Logan.

In Mandamus. On relators’ motion for an order for respondents to show cause why they should not be held in contempt and an order setting a court-supervised mediation. The motion for respondents to show cause is granted and the request for court-supervised mediation is held in abeyance. Respondents shall appear before the court on April 30, 2014, at 9:00 a.m. for a show-cause hearing. Relators may also appear for the hearing.

Lanzinger, Kennedy, and French, JJ., dissent.
